Author: CAMPBELL
Vol / Page: Bk4/4/269
Edition:
Quote:  In vain my protestations.  `Taihoa, taihoa, all in good time - what's the hurry, O Pakeha!' time was made for slaves - hurry no man's cattle, as we in the classics say. `What's the odds, a day or two sooner or later? There's Motu-Korea; it won't run away - taihoa nei?' with a chuck back of the head as they ended with the interrogative.
